Harry and Meghan spent Christmas of 2019 in Canada, before stepping down from senior royal duties the following month. And not only were they absent from the Royal Family dinner table that Christmas, a picture of the couple that had been there the year before was no longer on the table during the Queen's speech. Former editor of Vanity Fair, Tina Brown said in her new biography, The Palace Papers, that Prince William feared this move would cause his brother to have a tantrum. She said: "William was said to have been appalled when he saw the Sussexes had been edited out. He knew his brother well enough to predict a Category 5 tantrum brewing." FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES... 